Package stream.expression

Provides classes for parsing and evaluating expressions.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArithmeticExpression
    An ArithmeticExpression represents an arithmetic expression.
    BinaryOperation
    A BinaryOperation represents a binary operation.
    Division
    A Division represents a division operation.
    EqualTo
    An EqualTo represents a binary equality operation.
    Expression
    An ArithmeticExpression represents an arithmetic expression.
    GreaterThan
    A GreaterThan represents a binary operation that returns true if the left operand is greater than the right operand.
    LessThan
    A LessThan represents a binary operation that returns true if the left operand is less than the right operand.
    LogicalExpression
    An ArithmeticExpression represents an arithmetic expression.
    Multiplication
    A Multipliction represents a binary mulitplication operation.
    Negation
    A Negation represents a negation operation.
    Node
    A Node represents a node in a parse tree.
    StringTokenizer
    A StringTokenizer parses a string into tokens.
    Variable
    A Variable represents a variable in an expression.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ParsingException
    A ParsingException is thrown if an error occurs while parsing an expression.
    UnboundVariableException
    An UnboundVariableException is thrown if an expression being evaluated has a variable whose value is not set.
    UnregisteredVariableException
    An UnregisteredVariableException is thrown if an unregistered variable is referenced.
